
Play output TS on any supported media player in the system

Usage: tsp -O play [options]

Options:

  -f
  --ffplay
      Use ffplay (part of ffmpeg) for rendering. The default is to look for
      vlc, mplayer, ffplay, xine, in this order, and use the first available
      one.

  --help
      Display this help text.

  -m
  --mplayer
      Use mplayer for rendering. The default is to look for vlc, mplayer,
      ffplay, xine, in this order, and use the first available one.

  -x
  --xine
      Use xine for rendering. The default is to look for vlc, mplayer, ffplay,
      xine, in this order, and use the first available one.

